   science:"Brain scans show <span class='hl'>virtually all areas of the brain are active</span> — even during sleep. Different regions handle different tasks, but there are no large dormant areas waiting to be 'unlocked.' Brain damage to even small areas causes significant deficits, proving every part matters.",
